whats it like getting your tongue pierced omg finally after years of pursuasion my mum has agreed for me to get my tongue pierced but theres problem im really worried bout how much it'll hurt my bf has it done and he says it doesnt hurt at all just feels tingly then aches after with abit of swelling but im still worried really want it done but having doubts n really dnt wanna end up chickenin out help well there's quite a lot of negative responses on here so i'll give you a positive reply i've just had mine done a week ago it felt uncomfortable at the time after all they clamped a small area of the tongue to thin it down then pushed the piercing through the worst part of the whole experience for me though was the inability to swallow whilst it was being done as soon as the clamp went on i produced loads of saliva bled a little but as the assistant had a hold of the clamp i couldn't bring my tongue back in to swallow any whole thing took less than minutes though and after that the first day was a little uncomfortable there's some good hints to follow though ice crush some ice and allow it to melt on the tongue around the piercing to take the swelling down salt water make sure for the first couple of days that you swill saline solution salt water times a day to help remove infection mouthwash use a mouthwash for extra cleanliness make sure that it's a non alcoholic one though avoid alcohol hot spicy foods for weeks i had mine done days ago my swelling went down after only days by which time i was eating more or less normally the bar that the shop put in is quite large now and feels a little weird but once the regular tongue bar's back in i apparently won't really notice that i have a piercing there i'd say get it done it's not a bad thing at all Body piercing Halitosis Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Oral sex Social rule Electrophysiology 1957 World Series Piccolo Junior Saga Cocaine Dialysis Shaggy dog story Drowning Glossitis Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Wat